      • create

        public RepositoryVersionEntity create(StackEntity stackEntity,
                                      String version,
                                      String displayName,
                                      List<RepoOsEntity> repoOsEntities)
                               throws org.apache.ambari.server.AmbariException
        Validates and creates an object. The version must be unique within this stack name (e.g., HDP, HDPWIN, BIGTOP).
        Parameters:
        stackEntity - Stack entity.
        version - Stack version, e.g., 2.2 or 2.2.0.1-885
        displayName - Unique display name
        repoOsEntities - structure of repository URLs for each OS
        Returns:
        Returns the object created if successful, and throws an exception otherwise.
        Throws:
        org.apache.ambari.server.AmbariException

      • findRepositoriesWithVersionDefinitions

        public List<RepositoryVersionEntity> findRepositoriesWithVersionDefinitions()
        Retrieves repository version when they are loaded by a version definition file. This will not return all repositories - it will only return those which have a non-NULL VDF.
        Returns:
        a list of repositories created by VDF, or an empty list when there are none.
